  "system": {
    "description": "<h3>Weapon</h3><p>Upgrade Points:</p><p>F</p><h3>Double</h3><p>The firearm has two triggers that can be depressed at the same time, to perform a double-fire attack, or one at a time to perform two single attacks, such as single shot or potshots.</p><h3>Black Powder</h3><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Black powder firearms are firearms that instead of using preassembled cartridges load the bullet and gunpowder in the gun’s barrel or cylinder.<br></span></p><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The benefits to black powder are as long as a character has access to the bare materials, they can still use the weapon, and the weapon can have individualized powder charges per barrel or cylinder. The downsides are that black powder firearms are much slower to reload, can become unreliable if rained on or otherwise exposed to the weather, and if the charge isn’t loaded correctly, can cause the shot to fizzle, or even explode in the user’s face. Because of how black powder weapons work, the error range determines if the weapon goes off when it is fired.<br></span></p><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Because the powder has to be loaded manually, a black powder firearm can be loaded in one of three configurations:<br></span></p><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">• </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Light Load </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Grants -1 damage die but reduces the Error Range by 10%,<br></span></p><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">• </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Normal Load </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Grants no bonus or penalties<br></span></p><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">• </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Heavy Load </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Grants +1 damage die, but increases the weapon’s Error Range by 15%. If a black powder weapon is loaded heavily, and fails its Error Range check, it explodes and causes 1d8 slashing damage to its user, as well as destroying the firearm.<br></span></p><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">One pound of powder provides 30 normal loads. A light load counts as half a normal load and a heavy load counts as two normal loads. The Black Powder Firearms Proficiency feat is required to load black powder firearms, and use them without a -4 attack penalty, however, any character with the Personal Firearms Proficiency can use a Black Powder weapon without penalty, but cannot reload them.<br></span></p><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Black powder firearms can fit into standard firearms holsters, so as long as they would fit normally. All black powder firearms come with loading equipment for the specified model of firearm.<br></span></p><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Because of their design, black powder firearms can accept Enchantments directly onto the weapon, as well as the ammunition.<br></span></p><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">All black powder firearms calibers are considered 2nd category for the purpose of gunsmithing, and are restricted to single shot, double shot, single action revolver, double action only revolver, and double action revolver styles of firearm.</span></p>",
